{:itonami.blueprint/id "cloud-itonami-8220"
 :itonami.blueprint/name "Community Call Centre Operations"
 :itonami.blueprint/isic-rev5 "8220"
 :itonami.blueprint/domain :commercial/call-centre-services
 :itonami.blueprint/license "AGPL-3.0-or-later"
 :itonami.blueprint/social-impact [:data-privacy :worker-safety :local-jobs]
 :itonami.blueprint/governor :call-centre-governor
 :itonami.blueprint/robotics true
 :itonami.blueprint/required-technologies [:robotics :identity :forms :dmn :bpmn :audit-ledger :labor]
 :itonami.blueprint/optional-technologies [:optimization]
 :itonami.blueprint/status :public-oss
 :itonami.blueprint/maturity :implemented
 :itonami.blueprint/implemented-slice
 "CallCentreAdvisor ⊣ CallCentreGovernor (three HARD, permanent,
 un-overridable checks: campaign-unverified, effect-not-propose, and a
 combined closed-op-allowlist + scope-exclusion scan blocking any
 proposal that drifts into finalizing a data-privacy-compliance
 decision), a real compiled langgraph-clj StateGraph (langgraph.graph,
 callcentreops.operation/build: intake -> advise -> govern -> decide
 -> commit | request-approval -> commit | hold), a 0-3 rollout-phase
 gate (callcentreops.phase/gate), and an append-only audit ledger +
 committed-operations log (callcentreops.store/append-ledger! +
 commit-record!, both a MemStore defrecord and a DatomicStore backed
 by langchain.db via langchain-store.core). A back-office OPERATIONS
 COORDINATION actor for a call-centre service provider running
 inbound support and outbound telemarketing campaigns -- not
 data-privacy-compliance-decision authority (a do-not-call-list
 override, a consent-withdrawal resolution, a GDPR/CCPA compliance
 ruling, a data-breach determination all stay exclusively human, per
 ADR-2607152500's Wave-4 person-facing-service guardrail). Four ops
 (`:log-call-record` / `:schedule-staffing-operation` /
 `:coordinate-equipment-supply` / `:flag-privacy-concern`), all
 `:effect :propose` only. `:flag-privacy-concern` ALWAYS escalates to
 a human campaign supervisor via the compiled graph's
 `:request-approval` node (`interrupt-before`, checkpoint-based
 resume) at every phase, never auto-commit-eligible; the other three
 ops auto-commit only once phase 3 (supervised-auto) is reached and
 the Governor is clean. Every commit/hold/approval-rejected decision
 lands in the append-only ledger -- 50 tests / 158 assertions green
 (`clojure -M:dev:test`) covering the governor's hard checks, the
 scope-exclusion self-trip regression, phase gating, MemStore ≡
 DatomicStore parity, and a full compiled-StateGraph integration suite
 (clean commit, escalate→approve→commit, escalate→reject→hold, and
 four independent HARD-hold paths); demo runnable end-to-end
 (`clojure -M:run`)."}
